---
// ABOUTME: Landing page for keytun - keyboard tunnel for developers.
// ABOUTME: NuPhy-inspired design with keycap aesthetics and terminal vibes.
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="description" content="keytun - Lightweight keyboard tunnel for developers. Think ngrok, but for keystrokes." />
		<title>keytun - keyboard tunnel for developers</title>

		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
		<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
	</head>
	<body>
		<!-- Nav -->
		<nav>
			<div class="nav-inner">
				<a href="/" class="logo">
					<span class="logo-key">⌨</span> keytun
				</a>
				<div class="nav-links">
					<a href="#how-it-works">How it works</a>
					<a href="#install">Install</a>
					<a href="https://github.com/gbostoen/keytun" class="nav-github">GitHub</a>
					<button class="theme-toggle" id="theme-toggle" aria-label="Toggle dark mode">
						<span class="toggle-icon toggle-sun">☀</span>
						<span class="toggle-icon toggle-moon">☾</span>
					</button>
				</div>
			</div>
		</nav>

		<!-- Hero -->
		<section class="hero">
			<div class="hero-badge">Think ngrok, but for keystrokes</div>
			<h1>
				Let your colleague<br />
				<span class="gradient-text">type into your terminal.</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="hero-sub">
				You're screensharing. They need to run a command. Stop dictating characters —
				give them a session code and let them type directly.
			</p>
			<div class="hero-actions">
				<a href="#install" class="btn btn-primary">
					<span class="btn-icon">↓</span> Install keytun
				</a>
				<a href="#how-it-works" class="btn btn-ghost">See how it works</a>
			</div>

			<!-- Terminal demo -->
			<div class="terminal-wrap">
				<div class="terminal">
					<div class="terminal-bar">
						<div class="terminal-dots">
							<span class="dot dot-red"></span>
							<span class="dot dot-yellow"></span>
							<span class="dot dot-green"></span>
						</div>
						<span class="terminal-title">Terminal — host</span>
					</div>
					<div class="terminal-body">
						<div class="line"><span class="prompt">$</span> keytun host</div>
						<div class="line output">  keytun v0.1.0</div>
						<div class="line output session">  Session: <span class="code-highlight">keen-fox-42</span></div>
						<div class="line output">  Waiting for client... (share the code with your colleague)</div>
						<div class="line output dim"></div>
						<div class="line output peer-event">  ✓ Client connected</div>
						<div class="line"><span class="prompt">$</span> <span class="typing-text">docker compose up -d</span><span class="cursor">█</span></div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="terminal terminal-client">
					<div class="terminal-bar">
						<div class="terminal-dots">
							<span class="dot dot-red"></span>
							<span class="dot dot-yellow"></span>
							<span class="dot dot-green"></span>
						</div>
						<span class="terminal-title">Terminal — helper</span>
					</div>
					<div class="terminal-body">
						<div class="line"><span class="prompt">$</span> keytun join keen-fox-42</div>
						<div class="line output">  Connected to <span class="code-highlight">keen-fox-42</span></div>
						<div class="line output">  You are now typing into the remote terminal.</div>
						<div class="line output dim">  Press Ctrl+] to disconnect.</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Problem -->
		<section class="section" id="problem">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>The problem with screensharing</h2>
				<div class="problem-grid">
					<div class="problem-card">
						<div class="keycap keycap-bad">🗣</div>
						<h3>Dictating commands</h3>
						<p>"Capital D, dash, dash, no-cache, space, dot, no the other dot..."</p>
					</div>
					<div class="problem-card">
						<div class="keycap keycap-bad">🔄</div>
						<h3>Swapping screen control</h3>
						<p>Request control, wait for approval, fumble with resolution differences, give it back.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="problem-card">
						<div class="keycap keycap-bad">🛠</div>
						<h3>Full pair-programming tools</h3>
						<p>VS Code Live Share, tmate, tmux — all overkill for "let me just type this one command."</p>
					</div>
					<div class="problem-card solution">
						<div class="keycap keycap-good">⌨</div>
						<h3>keytun</h3>
						<p>Share a code. They type. You see it live on your screenshare. Done.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- How it works -->
		<section class="section section-dark" id="how-it-works">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>How it works</h2>
				<div class="architecture">
					<div class="arch-node">
						<div class="arch-keycap">
							<span>Host</span>
						</div>
						<p>Developer screensharing.<br />Runs <code>keytun host</code></p>
					</div>
					<div class="arch-arrow">
						<div class="arrow-line"></div>
						<span class="arrow-label">WebSocket</span>
					</div>
					<div class="arch-node arch-relay">
						<div class="arch-keycap arch-keycap-accent">
							<span>Relay</span>
						</div>
						<p>Stateless broker.<br />Bridges connections.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="arch-arrow">
						<div class="arrow-line"></div>
						<span class="arrow-label">WebSocket</span>
					</div>
					<div class="arch-node">
						<div class="arch-keycap">
							<span>Client</span>
						</div>
						<p>Helper colleague.<br />Runs <code>keytun join &lt;code&gt;</code></p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="steps">
					<div class="step">
						<div class="step-num keycap-small">1</div>
						<div class="step-content">
							<h3>Host starts a session</h3>
							<p>Run <code>keytun host</code>. A PTY spawns your shell. You get a session code like <code>keen-fox-42</code>.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="step">
						<div class="step-num keycap-small">2</div>
						<div class="step-content">
							<h3>Share the code over your call</h3>
							<p>Session codes use words — easy to read aloud. "keen fox forty-two."</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="step">
						<div class="step-num keycap-small">3</div>
						<div class="step-content">
							<h3>Helper joins and types</h3>
							<p>Raw key bytes flow through the relay to the host's PTY. Arrow keys, tab completion, Ctrl+C — everything works.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="step">
						<div class="step-num keycap-small">4</div>
						<div class="step-content">
							<h3>Host sees it live</h3>
							<p>Both local and remote input appear in the same terminal. Your screenshare shows everything in real time.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Features -->
		<section class="section" id="features">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Built for developers</h2>
				<div class="features-grid">
					<div class="feature">
						<div class="keycap-small feature-icon">⚡</div>
						<h3>Single binary</h3>
						<p>Go binary. No runtime, no dependencies. Download and run.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="feature">
						<div class="keycap-small feature-icon">🔑</div>
						<h3>Readable session codes</h3>
						<p>Wordlist-based codes like <code>keen-fox-42</code>. Easy to say over a call.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="feature">
						<div class="keycap-small feature-icon">🖥</div>
						<h3>Full terminal fidelity</h3>
						<p>Raw bytes, not characters. Arrow keys, Ctrl sequences, tab completion all preserved.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="feature">
						<div class="keycap-small feature-icon">🔒</div>
						<h3>Secure by design</h3>
						<p>Sessions are explicit. Host sees a banner on connect. Ctrl+C kills the session instantly.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="feature">
						<div class="keycap-small feature-icon">☁️</div>
						<h3>Self-hostable relay</h3>
						<p>Stateless WebSocket broker. Deploy on Fly.io, Railway, or any container host.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="feature">
						<div class="keycap-small feature-icon">🪶</div>
						<h3>Lightweight</h3>
						<p>No database, no auth tokens, no persistence. Sessions live in memory.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Install -->
		<section class="section section-dark" id="install">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Get started</h2>
				<div class="install-grid">
					<div class="install-card">
						<h3>With Go</h3>
						<div class="install-terminal">
							<code>go install github.com/gbostoen/keytun@latest</code>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="install-card">
						<h3>From source</h3>
						<div class="install-terminal">
							<code>git clone https://github.com/gbostoen/keytun.git<br />cd keytun<br />make build</code>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="usage-example">
					<h3>Usage</h3>
					<div class="usage-grid">
						<div class="usage-block">
							<span class="usage-label">Host (developer)</span>
							<div class="install-terminal">
								<code>keytun host</code>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="usage-block">
							<span class="usage-label">Client (helper)</span>
							<div class="install-terminal">
								<code>keytun join keen-fox-42</code>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="usage-block">
							<span class="usage-label">Self-host relay</span>
							<div class="install-terminal">
								<code>keytun relay --addr :8080</code>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Protocol -->
		<section class="section" id="protocol">
			<div class="container">
				<h2>Simple protocol</h2>
				<p class="section-sub">JSON over WebSocket. Five message types. That's it.</p>
				<div class="protocol-grid">
					<div class="protocol-msg">
						<span class="msg-direction">Host → Relay</span>
						<code class="msg-type">host_register</code>
						<p>Register a session code</p>
					</div>
					<div class="protocol-msg">
						<span class="msg-direction">Client → Relay</span>
						<code class="msg-type">client_join</code>
						<p>Join an existing session</p>
					</div>
					<div class="protocol-msg">
						<span class="msg-direction">Client → Host</span>
						<code class="msg-type">input</code>
						<p>Base64-encoded key bytes</p>
					</div>
					<div class="protocol-msg">
						<span class="msg-direction">Host → Client</span>
						<code class="msg-type">output</code>
						<p>PTY output for remote echo</p>
					</div>
					<div class="protocol-msg">
						<span class="msg-direction">Relay → Both</span>
						<code class="msg-type">peer_event</code>
						<p>joined / left notifications</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Footer -->
		<footer>
			<div class="container footer-inner">
				<div class="footer-logo">
					<span class="logo-key">⌨</span> keytun
				</div>
				<p>Lightweight keyboard tunnel for developers.</p>
				<div class="footer-links">
					<a href="https://github.com/gbostoen/keytun">GitHub</a>
					<span class="footer-sep">·</span>
					<a href="https://github.com/gbostoen/keytun/issues">Issues</a>
					<span class="footer-sep">·</span>
					<a href="https://github.com/gbostoen/keytun/releases">Releases</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</footer>
		<script>
			const toggle = document.getElementById('theme-toggle');
			const html = document.documentElement;

			// Check for saved preference, then system preference
			const saved = localStorage.getItem('theme');
			if (saved) {
				html.setAttribute('data-theme', saved);
			} else if (window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches) {
				html.setAttribute('data-theme', 'dark');
			}

			toggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
				const current = html.getAttribute('data-theme');
				const next = current === 'dark' ? 'light' : 'dark';
				html.setAttribute('data-theme', next);
				localStorage.setItem('theme', next);
			});
		</script>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	/* ---- Reset & Base ---- */
	*, *::before, *::after {
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	:root {
		/* NuPhy accent colors - warm keycap tones (shared) */
		--accent-coral: #e8544e;
		--accent-peach: #e87a54;
		--accent-amber: #e8a830;
		--accent-mint: #3da854;
		--accent-lavender: #8b6ce0;
		--accent-sky: #2f9ec4;

		--gradient-primary: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-coral), var(--accent-peach), var(--accent-amber));
		--gradient-cool: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-sky), var(--accent-lavender));

		--radius: 12px;
		--radius-sm: 8px;

		--font-sans: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
		--font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;

		/* Light theme (default) */
		--bg: #ffffff;
		--bg-surface: #f5f5f7;
		--bg-card: #ffffff;
		--bg-elevated: #f0f0f2;

		--text: #1d1d1f;
		--text-dim: #6e6e73;
		--text-muted: #a1a1a6;

		--border: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
		--border-accent: rgba(232, 84, 78, 0.25);

		--keycap-shadow: 0 3px 0 #d1d1d6, 0 5px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
		--keycap-shadow-sm: 0 2px 0 #d1d1d6, 0 3px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);

		--terminal-bg: #1d1d1f;
		--terminal-bar: #2c2c2e;
		--terminal-border: rgba(0,0,0,0.1);

		--nav-bg: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		--nav-border: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);

		--code-bg: #f0f0f2;
		--code-color: var(--accent-coral);
		--code-border: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);

		--btn-primary-text: #ffffff;
		--btn-ghost-border: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
		--btn-ghost-hover-border: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
		--btn-primary-hover-shadow: 0 4px 0 #d1d1d6, 0 8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
		--btn-primary-active-shadow: 0 1px 0 #d1d1d6, 0 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);

		--badge-bg: rgba(232, 84, 78, 0.08);
		--badge-border: rgba(232, 84, 78, 0.15);

		--solution-bg: rgba(232, 122, 84, 0.06);
		--solution-border: rgba(232, 122, 84, 0.25);

		--msg-type-bg: rgba(232, 84, 78, 0.08);
		--msg-type-border: rgba(232, 84, 78, 0.12);

		--link-color: var(--accent-sky);
		--link-hover: var(--accent-coral);
	}

	[data-theme="dark"] {
		--bg: #1a1a2e;
		--bg-surface: #16213e;
		--bg-card: #1f2b47;
		--bg-elevated: #253555;

		--text: #e8e8e8;
		--text-dim: #8892a4;
		--text-muted: #5a6478;

		--accent-coral: #ff6b6b;
		--accent-peach: #ffa07a;
		--accent-amber: #ffd93d;
		--accent-mint: #6bcb77;
		--accent-lavender: #a78bfa;
		--accent-sky: #4cc9f0;

		--gradient-primary: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-coral), var(--accent-peach), var(--accent-amber));

		--border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		--border-accent: rgba(255, 160, 122, 0.3);

		--keycap-shadow: 0 3px 0 #0d1117, 0 5px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
		--keycap-shadow-sm: 0 2px 0 #0d1117, 0 3px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);

		--terminal-bg: #0d1117;
		--terminal-bar: #161b22;
		--terminal-border: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);

		--nav-bg: rgba(26, 26, 46, 0.85);
		--nav-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);

		--code-bg: #253555;
		--code-color: var(--accent-peach);
		--code-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);

		--btn-primary-text: #1a1a2e;
		--btn-ghost-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
		--btn-ghost-hover-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
		--btn-primary-hover-shadow: 0 4px 0 #0d1117, 0 8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
		--btn-primary-active-shadow: 0 1px 0 #0d1117, 0 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);

		--badge-bg: rgba(255, 160, 122, 0.1);
		--badge-border: rgba(255, 160, 122, 0.2);

		--solution-bg: rgba(255, 160, 122, 0.05);
		--solution-border: rgba(255, 160, 122, 0.3);

		--msg-type-bg: rgba(255, 160, 122, 0.1);
		--msg-type-border: rgba(255, 160, 122, 0.15);

		--link-color: var(--accent-sky);
		--link-hover: var(--accent-peach);
	}

	html {
		scroll-behavior: smooth;
	}

	body {
		font-family: var(--font-sans);
		background: var(--bg);
		color: var(--text);
		line-height: 1.6;
		-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
	}

	a {
		color: var(--link-color);
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: color 0.2s;
	}

	a:hover {
		color: var(--link-hover);
	}

	code {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 0.9em;
		background: var(--code-bg);
		padding: 2px 7px;
		border-radius: 5px;
		color: var(--code-color);
		border: 1px solid var(--code-border);
	}

	/* On gray surface sections, make inline code pop with a white bg */
	.section-dark code {
		background: var(--bg);
		border-color: var(--border);
	}

	.container {
		max-width: 1100px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 24px;
	}

	/* ---- Nav ---- */
	nav {
		position: fixed;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		right: 0;
		z-index: 100;
		background: var(--nav-bg);
		backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--nav-border);
	}

	.nav-inner {
		max-width: 1100px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 24px;
		height: 64px;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
	}

	.logo {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--text);
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 6px;
	}

	.logo:hover {
		color: var(--text);
	}

	.logo-key {
		font-size: 1.3rem;
	}

	.nav-links {
		display: flex;
		gap: 28px;
		align-items: center;
	}

	.nav-links a {
		color: var(--text-dim);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.nav-links a:hover {
		color: var(--text);
	}

	.nav-github {
		background: var(--bg-elevated);
		padding: 6px 14px;
		border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 0.85rem !important;
	}

	.nav-github:hover {
		background: var(--bg-card);
	}

	/* ---- Hero ---- */
	.hero {
		padding: 140px 24px 80px;
		text-align: center;
		max-width: 1100px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.hero-badge {
		display: inline-block;
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: var(--accent-coral);
		background: var(--badge-bg);
		border: 1px solid var(--badge-border);
		padding: 6px 18px;
		border-radius: 50px;
		margin-bottom: 28px;
	}

	.hero h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4rem);
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.15;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.gradient-text {
		background: var(--gradient-primary);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.hero-sub {
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		color: var(--text-dim);
		max-width: 600px;
		margin: 0 auto 36px;
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	.hero-actions {
		display: flex;
		gap: 16px;
		justify-content: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		margin-bottom: 64px;
	}

	.btn {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		padding: 14px 28px;
		border-radius: var(--radius);
		font-weight: 600;
		font-size: 1rem;
		transition: all 0.2s;
		cursor: pointer;
	}

	.btn-primary {
		background: var(--gradient-primary);
		color: var(--btn-primary-text);
		box-shadow: var(--keycap-shadow);
	}

	.btn-primary:hover {
		transform: translateY(-1px);
		box-shadow: var(--btn-primary-hover-shadow);
